  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to perform an evaluation of a trauma-focused short-term
      intervention (Narrative Exposure Therapy; Schauer, M., Neuner, F. &amp; Elbert, T.) on a variety
      of clinical outcome measures (PTSD, Depression, Somatic Complaints, Dissociation) in women
      after sexual exploitation and women trafficking.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
